  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3476",
  "title": "Arbitrary template variables",
  "body": "**Feature request 🙏**\r\nI would like to be able to pass an object of template variables into custom templates so I don't need to write custom render functions for widgets\r\n\r\nSomething that would look like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nrefinementList({\r\n  container: '.container',\r\n  templates: {\r\n    item: myItemTemplate,\r\n    templateData: {\r\n      foo: 'bar'\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere `foo` is exposed for use inside the Handlebars template along with existing vars:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// myItemTemplate.hbs\r\n<p>{{label}} ({{count}}) - {{ foo }}</p>\r\n```",
